        {
          "id": 3217889392,
          "type": "DiffNote",
          "body": "The only \"conventions\" in these files are ones we define, we can move things around to whatever makes the most sense.\n\nLike I said, Gainwell is going to roll these out in this manner workspace by workspace - see [DSP-8007](https://abacusinsights.atlassian.net/browse/DSP-8007), [DSP-8008](https://abacusinsights.atlassian.net/browse/DSP-8008), [DSP-8009](https://abacusinsights.atlassian.net/browse/DSP-8009), [DSP-8010](https://abacusinsights.atlassian.net/browse/DSP-8010) filed just today. Given that, and especially given that two of Nevada's workspaces here are moving to 9115+0057 and one of them is staying at just 9115, I thought it made sense to group the IGs into the two groups that will be repeated in whatever combination. If you think that's too confusing, I suppose we can get rid of the anchor tags altogether and be explicit about it, that just felt like ~500 extra lines of redundant code for no reason.",
          "author": {
            "id": 5938765,
            "username": "srosenfeld",
            "public_email": "",
            "name": "Steve Rosenfeld",
            "state": "active",
            "locked": false,
            "avatar_url": "https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/25c818116c8ce2c185043ca59ff2a1e141a9f8211eeb4dd1248b9dc41b734527?s=80&d=identicon",
